<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,289,566]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,505,529]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[645,721,505,529]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aculus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[645,721,505,529]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Aculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
? by 
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine" box="[775,1072,505,529]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. (1994) Catalog of the Eriophyoidea (Acarina: Prostigmata) of the World. Indira Publish. House, West Bloomfield, Michigan, USA, 804 pp." type="book" year="1994">
Amrine and Stasny (
<number box="[1003,1064,505,529]" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" value="1994.0">1994</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, details of the anterior lobe and the dorsal semiannuli suggest the assignment to 
<taxonomicName box="[794,884,541,565]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aculops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="10" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[794,884,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">Aculops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in agreement with Amrine (
<emphasis box="[1202,1303,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="57">in litteris</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
